        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 4 at 6:30PM MDT by NWS North Platte NE</headline>
        <description>At 630 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms near Pleasant Valley, or 9 miles southeast of Holyoke,
moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Imperial, Lamar, Champion, Crete, Chase, and Wanamaker State Wildfire
Management Area.

This includes Highway 61 between mile markers 44 and 52.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
